Sentencas: Low temperature, 300-600 degrees C solid oxide fuel cell (LTSOFC) is one of the hot areas in recent fuel cell development.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of hierarchical porous LiNiCuZn-oxides as potential electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In order to develop high performance LTSOFCs, compatible electrodes are highly demanded.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of hierarchical porous LiNiCuZn-oxides as potential electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this work, a lithium transition metal oxide electrode material with hierarchical porous structure was synthesized.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of hierarchical porous LiNiCuZn-oxides as potential electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The phase structure was analysed by XRD and microstructure was studied by SEM.
Titulo: Synthesis and characterization of hierarchical porous LiNiCuZn-oxides as potential electrode materials for low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The as-synthesized material was constructed to devices using the SDC (samarium doped ceria)-carbonate nanocomposite (NSDC) as the electrolyte to test the OCV (open circuit voltage), which indicates good catalytic performance for H-2 at 600 degrees C.
